HtmlItemData.Html:
Employee Benefits Survey
 
 
 
The following survey looks to identify the range of benefits offered to you by your employer.  We would appreciate you taking a few minutes to answer the following questions.  Thank you.

Insurance benefits
 
For each of the following Insurance benefits, please select whether your employer fully pays or part pays these costs.  Please also detail if these benefits are, in fact offered by your employer.

ItemTexts_Select1Data.TextValue: How long have you worked for your current employer?
What type of employee are you?
What is your current annual income?
Which age group do you belong to?
What is the maximum number of days that can be carried over into the next year?
Can employees trade accrued days for pay?
Does your employer offer any kind of Performance related bonus or Incentive programs?
Does your employer offer either an Employee Stock Option Program (ESOP) or an Employee Profit Sharing Program?
Does your employer offer either a 401k or 403b program for retirement savings?
Does your employer match your contributions?
Does your employer require a minimum contribution by yourself before they will contribute the match?
Overall, how satisfied are you with the benefits offered by your employer?

OptionTexts.TextValue: Offered to Full time employees only

ItemTexts_MessageItemData.TextValue: Thank you for taking the time to complete this survey.

ItemTexts_MatrixItemData.TextValue: What benefits are offered to you by your employer?
Please select which of the following, if any, are offered by your employer:

MatrixCategoryTexts.TextValue: Cafeteria, meal subsidies, free snacks or beverages

ItemTexts_MultiLineTextItemData.TextValue: Please detail any other insurance benefits offered by your employer and who covers the cost of these benefits:
Please provide details of any performance related or incentive programs:
Please provide details on the Employee Stock Option Program(ESOP)or Employee Profit Sharing Program:
